Here's a step-by-step guide on how to deploy a React Native app to TestFlight:

1. Create an App Store Connect account and enroll in the Apple Developer Program (if you haven't already).

2. Open Xcode and create a new project or open your existing React Native project. Make sure you have the latest version of Xcode installed.

3. In your React Native project, add the following lines to your `App.js` file:

```javascript
import { AppRegistry } from 'react-native';
import RNFetchBlob from 'rn-fetch-blob';
import App from './App';
import { name as appName } from './app.json';

RNFetchBlob.config({
  sessionManager: 'smSession',
});

AppRegistry.registerComponent(appName, () => App);
```

This will enable us to use the `rn-fetch-blob` library for uploading the app binary to TestFlight.

4. Install the `rn-fetch-blob` library by running `npm install rn-fetch-blob` in your terminal.

5. Create a new iOS distribution certificate and a new distribution provisioning profile using the Apple Developer Center. You can find instructions on how to do this here: https://docs.apple.com/appstoreconnect/distribution/index.html

6. Run the following command in your terminal to generate a release build of your app:

```bash
react-native run-ios --configuration Release
